A4.text: Dunstanburgh Castle is a 14th-century fortification on the coast of Northumberland in northern England

A5.text: Northumberland has more castles than any other county in England, including prominent ones at Alnwick, Bamburgh, Dunstanburgh, Newcastle, and Warkworth.

A6.text: Dunstanburgh Castle is between the villages of Craster and Embleton.

A7.text: The castle was built by Thomas, 2nd Earl of Lancaster between 1313 and 1322.
